HEADWORD: Electrophorus
<hw>E*lec`troph"o*rus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>\'d8Electrophori</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[NL., fr. combining form <ets>electro-</ets> + Gr.
<grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An
instrument for exciting electricity, and repeating the charge
indefinitely by induction, consisting of a flat cake of resin, shellac,
or ebonite, upon which is placed a plate of metal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electro-physiological</ent>⟦br⟧
